#Y = Beta0 + Beta1 x Garlic + Beta2 x Tomato + Beta3 x Broth + interactions + error term

# Regression Analysis
model_full = lm(Rating ~ Garlic * Tomato_Sauce * Chicken_Broth, data = rice_data)
print(model_full)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = Rating ~ Garlic * Tomato_Sauce * Chicken_Broth, 
##     data = rice_data)
## 
## Coefficients:
##                                (Intercept)  
##                                        7.5  
##                                  GarlicYes  
##                                        0.5  
##                            Tomato_SauceLow  
##                                        1.5  
##                           Chicken_BrothLow  
##                                       -3.5  
##                  GarlicYes:Tomato_SauceLow  
##                                       -3.0  
##                 GarlicYes:Chicken_BrothLow  
##                                       -0.5  
##           Tomato_SauceLow:Chicken_BrothLow  
##                                       -3.5  
## GarlicYes:Tomato_SauceLow:Chicken_BrothLow  
##                                        3.0
#lenths Method
# Step 1: Get effects 
effects = coef(model_full)[-1]  # exclude intercept

# Step 2: Compute absolute effects
abs_effects = abs(effects)

# Step 3: Compute s0
s0 = 1.5 * median(abs_effects)

# Step 4: Trim large effects for PSE
trimmed_effects = abs_effects[abs_effects < 2.5 * s0]

# Step 5: Compute PSE (pseudo standard error)
PSE = 1.5 * median(trimmed_effects)

# Step 6: Compute tPSE values
tPSE = abs_effects / PSE

# Step 7: Combine into a table
results = data.frame(
  Effect = names(effects),
  Estimate = effects,
  Abs_Effect = abs_effects,
  tPSE = tPSE
)

print(results)
##                                                                                Effect
## GarlicYes                                                                   GarlicYes

## Tomato_SauceLow:Chicken_BrothLow               -3.5        3.5 0.7777778
## GarlicYes:Tomato_SauceLow:Chicken_BrothLow      3.0        3.0 0.6666667
ier.crit = 2.3

results$Significant = abs(results$tPSE) > ier.crit
print(results$Significant)

#Half Normal Plot
dev.off()
## null device 
##           1
library(faraway)

thetaloc = function(I) {
  p = (0.5 + 0.5 * ((1:I) - 0.5) / I)
  qnorm(p) 
}

effects_abs_sorted = sort(abs_effects)
effect_labels = names(abs_effects)[order(abs_effects)]

x = thetaloc(length(effects_abs_sorted))
plot(x, effects_abs_sorted, 
     main = "Half-Normal Plot",
     xlab = "Half-Normal Quantiles",
     ylab = "Absolute Effects",
     pch = 19,
  abline(lm(effects_abs_sorted ~ x), col = "red", lwd = 2))

text(x, effects_abs_sorted, labels = effect_labels, pos = 3, cex = 0.8)
print(effect_labels)
